empty a file 
> <filename>


huge directories
du -ahsS  | sort -n -r | head -n 5

huge file sizes only 
find -type f -exec du -Sh {} + | sort -rh | head -n 5

Markdown basics https://www.markdownguide.org/basic-syntax/

* and _ are interchangable, use either for same effect

> for block quote
>
>> nested blockquote
** for bold
* and space for italic words
*word* to make letters in a word italic
***word*** for bold + italic


<number period space> for numbered lists and nested too
<hyphen space > for unordered lists   #  hyphen(-), asterisks (*), or plus signs (+) they all work   use \ to begin list with a number

URL with tooltip or title  If URL contains ( or ) use %28 to escape it 
[text](url "tooltip")
<> to turn  text into URL
Image [name](url "tooltip")

To add a link to an image, enclose the Markdown for the image in brackets, and then add the link in parentheses.

[![An old rock in the desert](/assets/images/shiprock.jpg "Shiprock, New Mexico by Beau Rogers")](https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/151925446?v=4)



`` for Code   to escape double backquote ``

horizontal lines 3 or more *** or ____ or ---



I love supporting the **[EFF](https://eff.org)**.
This is the *[Markdown Guide](https://www.markdownguide.org)*.
